children.subject: If you need a technical elective, you could consider non-CS courses as well? e.g. ee120, eecs126, eecs127, math/statistics courses, info/data courses, etc.

history.content: Anyone who finds themselves in OP's situation should contact cs-enrollments [at] berkeley [dot] edu to talk to Cindy Conners for assistance.

Hi all,

I am a current senior declared in Computer Science. I need one technical elective left to graduate and I cannot enroll in a single upper division CS class because all classes that I have not already taken are full. I am currently on the waitlist for 3 classes (even though I only need 1) and am getting concerned that I won't be able to get in. 

CS W182 - waitlisted at #108

CS171  - waitlisted at #24

CS194 - waitlisted at #47

Are there no reserved seats in these classes for graduating seniors? Are any of these classes going to open more seats? What are my options here so I can graduate this semester?
